  "2026-07-20T03:54:53.015Z",maintainer-agent,"Pre-push Greptile review 801a7677-68c3-4ee6-983a-2b42b8c1bb75 (confidence 3/5): accepted the durable-index status TOCTOU finding; byte size now derives from the exact decoded payload rather than a racing stat call. Focused durable-cache tests and strict static gates pass."
  "2026-07-20T04:04:17.668Z",maintainer-agent,"Review evidence: exact-head Greptile review 84ef563e-f412-44be-80e5-462936a5134d completed at confidence 5/5 with no actionable findings. It confirmed the durable cache atomic-write, fingerprint invalidation, status byte accounting, CLI contracts, and SDK coverage after the review fixes."
  "2026-07-20T04:17:11.570Z",maintainer-agent,"Final branch evidence before PR: 318 test files / 5,993 tests passed with exact 100% statements (40,144/40,144), branches (28,184/28,184), functions (8,148/8,148), and lines (39,084/39,084). All 10 linked tests passed, including full coverage, graph SDK/CLI contracts, VCS package acceptance, and strict static gates. Fresh packed-package temp proof installed 2026.7.19, rebuilt a two-item graph index, reused a query across processes, invalidated after mutation, and imported the public SDK to model custom company owns plus commit ordering relationships."
  "2026-07-20T04:53:49.127Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #622 review round 1: accepted Greptile P1 registry-semantic invalidation and CodeRabbit canonical rebuild warming. Workspace fingerprints now include stable full relationship-kind definitions and both graph/deps assembly paths consume that exact registry; rebuilding with unrelated query flags still warms plain summary keys. Accepted locale-independent new sort findings; declined Gemini's process-local durable-view cache because it would violate clear/rebuild and cross-process coherence. Final review-fix coverage: 318 files / 5,994 tests, exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-20T05:23:26.368Z",codex-root,"Review round 2 evidence: custom extension relationship kinds are now accepted by graph and deps context filters through the same resolved registry used for assembly/fingerprints. Deterministic governance sorting avoids JSON serialization and implicit tuple coercion. Full suite passes 5,995 tests with exact 100/100/100/100 coverage plus strict static gates."
  "2026-07-20T05:41:22.362Z",codex-root,"PR #622 final review round: hardened the durable SDK baseline schema for array/nested-count defects and preserved compatibility for pre-duplicateRows public assemblies. Per-type baseline drift is now a first-class signed delta. Exact full coverage and strict static gates pass."
  "2026-07-20T05:55:01.440Z",codex-root,"PR #622 durability review evidence: accepted Gemini concurrency and best-effort cache findings. Durable graph writes now acquire the shared cross-process lock for read-merge-atomic-write, so concurrent MCP/CLI completions retain both query entries; clear uses the same lock. Non-authoritative write failures no longer reject successful graph queries. Regressions cover concurrent writes and injected storage failure. Full suite: 318 files / 5,996 tests, exact 100/100/100/100 (40,184 statements; 28,239 branches; 8,154 functions; 39,121 lines); lint/static gates pass."
  "2026-07-20T06:10:05.658Z",codex-gpt5,"Final delayed-review remediation evidence: durable graph envelope decoding now rejects array-shaped results maps, invalid graph maintenance/baseline flag combinations are rejected before relationship-registry resolution, fingerprinting, or graph-cache assembly, and a spy-backed regression proves no workspace cache lookup occurs. Verification: focused durable-cache suite 10/10; pnpm lint passed (ESLint, zero jscpd clones, static quality, package-boundary, token-budget, 100% docstrings); full sandboxed coverage passed 318 files / 5,996 tests at 100% statements (40,184), branches (28,240), functions (8,154), and lines (39,121)."
  "2026-07-20T06:30:14.911Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #622 latest Gemini follow-up: accepted the case-folded duplicate-row ordering concern while preserving the project's locale-independent determinism rule. Duplicate governance rows now sort holder, target, and kind by lowercase canonical value with exact-spelling tie-breakers; regressions exercise case-only holder/target/kind ties. Focused governance 19/19, ESLint/static quality, zero-clone jscpd, 100% docstrings, package-boundary/token-budget, and full 318-file / 5,996-test coverage all pass at exact 100/100/100/100 (40,191 statements; 28,240 branches; 8,155 functions; 39,126 lines)."
  "2026-07-20T06:46:50.812Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #622 review follow-up: Gemini's two AuditNodeState findings were rejected after source verification because the interface declares id and nodeStates populates id from detail.id; no runtime defect exists. Gemini/CodeRabbit's shared legacy snapshot concern was accepted for direct public-SDK callers: per-type delta reads now tolerate pre-coverage_by_type baseline/current payloads, with regressions proving zero-based positive and negative typed deltas. Full strict verification: 318 files / 5,996 tests, exact 100% statements (40,194), branches (28,242), functions (8,156), lines (39,129); lint, zero-clone, static complexity, 100% docstrings, package boundary, and token budget pass."
  "2026-07-20T06:59:06.621Z",codex-wide-sdk,"Review-loop evidence: normalized graph item types at the SDK assembly boundary and in cache identity, preventing whitespace-only representation differences from splitting per-type governance or invalidating durable/memoized graph state. Focused graph tests passed (36/36); full repo coverage remains 100/100/100/100 across 5,996 tests."
  "2026-07-20T07:15:33.820Z",maintainer-agent,"Merged delivery evidence: PR #622 merged to main as e98282a1 with the durable cross-process graph index, extension-aware registry/cache semantics, baseline persistence, CLI/MCP/contracts/docs, and compatibility hardening. Exact-head review/check inventory was fully green and post-merge release/telemetry verification passed. This durable-index tranche is shipped; the feature returns open for migration/backfill and million-item conformance work already recorded in its metadata."
  "2026-07-21T18:22:44.680Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-21: advance the canonical relationship SDK with a rebuildable incremental graph/read-index seam shared with pm-801d, preserving source authority, deterministic bounded queries, and thin adapters. All-status lineage review reused pm-ju83; no duplicate was created."
  "2026-07-21T19:26:18.392Z",codex-root,"Graph/index tranche evidence: relationship graph reads now consume an effective metadata source cursor that includes the collapsed mutation delta, so supported relationship-field changes are visible to later CLI processes and long-lived SDK hosts without whole-store scans. CLI create/copy/restore import the projection contract through src/sdk/item-metadata-index.ts, satisfying the CLI-on-SDK boundary ratchet. GH-628 graph runner allocation cleanup is included. Focused graph/SDK/integration tests (205) and the exact 6071-test 100% coverage gate pass. This rolling relationship feature remains open for its broader 1M/custom-domain acceptance after this shipped tranche."
  "2026-07-21T19:53:07.376Z",codex-root,"Review-loop follow-up: CodeRabbit correctly identified that the public SDK facade should document its no-op lock and warning-token contracts, and that the real-lock regression test should derive its scale fixture from DEFAULT_DERIVED_INDEX_MINIMUM_ITEMS rather than hardcode 500. Applying both plus the related graph-doc wording correction on the current PR head."
  "2026-07-21T19:57:48.418Z",codex-root,"Review fixes verified: the SDK now exports and documents DEFAULT_DERIVED_INDEX_MINIMUM_ITEMS plus no-op-lock/warning behavior; the real-lock test derives 501 items from that contract; graph docs use the correct compound modifier. Focused SDK/index tests pass 132/132, pnpm lint passes with exact 100% docstrings and zero clones, typecheck passes, and docs links pass."
  "2026-07-21T20:41:56.983Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"Implementation start 2026-07-21: add a resumable deterministic legacy-item relationship backfill planner and atomic lock-serialized durable batch append. All-status lineage review reused pm-ju83; this directly targets its migration/backfill, immutable event, crash-safety, and custom-kind acceptance."
  "2026-07-21T20:55:28.255Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"TDD progress: the new public migration suite failed before implementation because planRelationshipEventBackfill and appendBatch did not exist. It now passes deterministic order-independent planning, custom ontology preservation, atomic validation/write failure rollback, concurrent identical resume, collision rejection, and a real 10,000-edge durable batch."
  "2026-07-21T21:15:17.718Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"Verification evidence 2026-07-21: focused linked relationship migration/history suite passed 31/31; literal all-source coverage passed 335 files and 6,076 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; packed @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.21 consumer imported planRelationshipEventBackfill and RelationshipEventStore from the public ./sdk export, planned two edges, atomically published version 2, resumed both identical events, and observed exactly two JSONL rows. Release gates also passed typecheck, docs, static/docstring, package-boundary, token-budget, secret scan, packed npx smoke, and 88-command package-first dogfood; the pre-commit Greptile stage correctly deferred because there were no committed changes yet."
  "2026-07-21T21:36:59.732Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"Committed-head release evidence 2026-07-21: all deterministic release gates passed at 3b8ae4b7, including exact all-source coverage, secret scan, packed npx smoke, and 88-command package-first dogfood. The external Greptile CLI could not run because its review quota is exhausted; canonical quota policy pm-e02lgu records that service condition while hosted bot triggers remain required when available."
  "2026-07-21T21:37:36.275Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"PR evidence: broad SDK relationship migration and atomic batch publication is under review in https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/639 at committed head 4e882672. Hosted checks and AI-review feedback will be evaluated against the exact current head before merge."
  "2026-07-21T21:43:56.114Z",codex-relationship-backfill-20260721,"Exact-head review closeout: PR #639 head a3ffacfb is mergeable and all deterministic GitHub checks are green. Every bot comment/review is reacted to and acknowledged; no unresolved thread or actionable finding remains. Gemini is sunset, Greptile/CodeRabbit/Sourcery were quota-limited, and those external conditions are tracked by pm-e02lgu. The feature returns open for remaining million-scale/pluggable-platform scope."
notes[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:19:35.648Z",codex-gpt5,"Remaining canonical scope after this PR: durable storage adapters, native CLI/MCP graph query integration, migration/backfill, and million-item storage validation; keep feature open."
  "2026-07-17T10:22:56.686Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation constraints recorded 2026-07-17 (review pass #96), two hard facts for whoever claims this slice. (1) src/sdk/runtime.ts gate headroom is 2 lines (census on pm-yh8r) — this slice's registry/graph-query exports CANNOT go through runtime.ts; ship the runtime partition first/with it, or route the new primitives through a dedicated subpath module (precedent: PR#571-lane sdk/test + sdk/diagnostics folders; sdk/query/ is the natural home). (2) Perf shape to fix while building the query primitives: pm deps --format context today assembles the FULL workspace RelationshipGraph + dangling-reference collection on every call (assembleDepsRelationshipGraph in src/sdk/dependencies.ts calls collectDanglingDependencyReferences + RelationshipGraph.fromItems over ALL items before bounding) — bounded output but unbounded assembly cost, O(all items) per invocation. The adjacency/bounded-subgraph primitives owned here are the natural place to make assembly incremental/indexed so bounded queries stop paying full-workspace cost; pm-m2il's scale matrix (query-budget axis) will measure it, pm-9rxu bl8x cache contract (CACHE_VERSION) is the substrate if an index is persisted."
  "2026-07-17T20:01:23.576Z",maintainer-agent,"Graph-query-surface lane continuation (2026-07-17, second tranche): pm graph grew communities/redundancy/dominators subcommands (11 total) as thin adapters over new sdk/graph/analytics.ts; hierarchyParentEndpoint/orderingPredecessorEndpoint promoted to module exports so analytics reuses traversal's semantic-orientation logic (single implementation, no clones). runtime.ts lost two now-unused runtime-input imports (isRecord, updateManyUpdateOptionsFromFlat) flagged by eslint after the partition. Test-lane fix: mcp-dynamic-package-actions impact assertion assumed pm_deps options.dep mutates — it never does (read projection); edge now created via pm_update, and the silent nested-options drop is filed as pm-upi0."
  "2026-07-17T21:43:59.589Z",maintainer-agent,"Sequencing constraint RELAXED (2026-07-17): the runtime.ts headroom-2 constraint cross-noted here and on pm-yh8r no longer binds — PR#580 extracted runtime-input.ts, runtime.ts now 3036/3400 gate-LOC (~364 headroom). ju83 remainder work (durable storage adapters, CLI/MCP graph query integration, migration/backfill, million-item validation) no longer requires a prior runtime partition. New gate-frontier files are cli/main.ts (15 headroom) and sdk/query/search.ts (29) — relevant only if ju83 wiring touches main.ts registration paths; prefer registering via register-list-query.ts/graph.ts shims as PR#580 did (graph.ts is a 7-line shim)."
  "2026-07-17T21:45:41.854Z",maintainer-agent,"Storage-adapter remainder design input (2026-07-17): external package unbraind/pm-graph (2026.7.15, neo4j-driver ^6.2.0, commands namespaced `pm-graph ping/export/cypher/sync/status/query/neighbors`) is the existing durable-graph-store exemplar — no command collision with native `pm graph` (verified). The adapter interface this item ships should let that package become a conforming backend (sync/export path) rather than a parallel model; related pm-7n5a owns the external Neo4j config surface."
  "2026-07-18T05:39:46.815Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#581 MERGED 2026-07-18 (second ju83 tranche): WorkspaceGraphCache (src/sdk/graph/cache.ts) — SHA-256 relationship-fingerprint keying, structured-clone isolated memoization, bounded LRU across workspaces, shared by all pm graph subcommands + pm deps --format context; resolves the recorded O(all-items) per-query deps-context assembly cost; cache{fingerprint,assembly,result} observability on every graph envelope. Remaining frontier unchanged in kind: durable storage adapters (pm-graph/Neo4j exemplar per note 5), rebuildable/crash-safe persistent indexes, migration/backfill of legacy kinds, and the million-item conformance run (shared with pm-m2il)."
  "2026-07-18T10:03:07.474Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#587 MERGED 2026-07-18 (third ju83-lineage tranche, SDK relationship event platform): extension-contributed relationship-kind registration/validation/composition (registerRelationshipKinds + RelationshipKindRegistry with direction, inverse, ordering, cardinality, lifecycle, aliases, version; strict contract rejects malformed containers), native workspace graph assembly now merges active package ontologies across CLI/MCP/SDK, bounded immutable RelationshipEventLog/RelationshipEventStore JSONL streams with reducer-based projections (in-memory + durable, point-in-time reads, checkpoint boundary documented), host-bound SDK injection into extension command handlers carrying caller authorship into durable events. Proven by the @unbrained/pm-vcs exemplar (pm-xtrd CLOSED). AC remainder UNCHANGED: durable storage adapters, persistent rebuildable indexes, migration/backfill, million-item validation — fingerprint still reads all items per one-shot invocation."
learnings[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T07:46:27.146Z",codex-gpt5-root,"A storage-independent relationship registry is the semantic boundary: algorithms must consume ordering/hierarchy flags rather than infer meaning from labels, while durable event/index implementations can remain interchangeable."
  "2026-07-14T10:02:20.502Z",codex-gpt5,Optimistic append sequences plus cursor fingerprints bind every page and snapshot to a coherent immutable relationship history; durable adapters can persist the same event contract without coupling graph semantics to storage.
  "2026-07-18T07:17:33.888Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,Extension commands must not recursively load extensions through their injected PmClient. The outer host already owns the active schema/registry context; use PmClient.forActiveExtensionHost so nested native lifecycle actions bypass activation queue reacquisition while retaining active registrations.
